<paragraph blockId="9.[151,1436,267,448]" pageId="9" pageNumber="46">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[197,323,383,409]" pageId="9" pageNumber="46">Diagnosis</emphasis>
. Aedeagus bifurcated from base, basally with 1 small, acute process (
<figureCitation box="[1198,1293,384,410]" captionStart="FIGURES 23–26" captionStartId="9.[151,271,1516,1540]" captionTargetBox="[239,1342,517,1470]" captionTargetId="figure-359@9.[188,1398,473,1514]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURES 23–26. Stegana (Steganina) pilosella sp. nov., ♂: 23. Epandrium, surstylus and cercus (lateral view); 24. surstylus (frontal view); 25. 10th sternite; 26. hypandrium, gonopods, aedeagus and aedeagal apodeme (ventral view) (For abbreviations see Figures 1–6. Scale bars: 0.1 mm)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5321880" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5321880/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="46">Fig. 26</figureCitation>
); gonopods broadened medially, with 2 slender projections sublaterally (
<figureCitation box="[859,947,422,448]" captionStart="FIGURES 23–26" captionStartId="9.[151,271,1516,1540]" captionTargetBox="[239,1342,517,1470]" captionTargetId="figure-359@9.[188,1398,473,1514]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURES 23–26. Stegana (Steganina) pilosella sp. nov., ♂: 23. Epandrium, surstylus and cercus (lateral view); 24. surstylus (frontal view); 25. 10th sternite; 26. hypandrium, gonopods, aedeagus and aedeagal apodeme (ventral view) (For abbreviations see Figures 1–6. Scale bars: 0.1 mm)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5321880" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5321880/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="46">Fig. 26</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
