<subSubSection lastPageId="10" lastPageNumber="47" pageId="9" pageNumber="46" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="9.[151,1436,1655,2029]" pageId="9" pageNumber="46">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[197,349,1655,1681]" pageId="9" pageNumber="46">Description.</emphasis>
Male and female: Pedicel grey-yellow; first flagellomere mostly black. Palpus mostly black. Katepisternum white-yellow, slightly brownish ventrally. Legs mostly brown, white on basal parts of all femora, black on distal parts of mid and hind femora and basal parts of mid and hind 1st tarsomeres, with 2 black rings on all tibiae. Abdominal 1st to 5th tergites black medially, yellow laterally; 6th nearly black. Sternites brown. Male terminalia: Epandrium with approximately 26 setae near posterior to ventral margin on each body-side (
<figureCitation box="[350,442,1849,1875]" captionStart="FIGURES 23–26" captionStartId="9.[151,271,1516,1540]" captionTargetBox="[239,1342,517,1470]" captionTargetId="figure-359@9.[188,1398,473,1514]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURES 23–26. Stegana (Steganina) pilosella sp. nov., ♂: 23. Epandrium, surstylus and cercus (lateral view); 24. surstylus (frontal view); 25. 10th sternite; 26. hypandrium, gonopods, aedeagus and aedeagal apodeme (ventral view) (For abbreviations see Figures 1–6. Scale bars: 0.1 mm)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5321880" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5321880/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="46">Fig. 23</figureCitation>
). Surstylus broadened (
<figureCitation box="[727,819,1849,1875]" captionStart="FIGURES 23–26" captionStartId="9.[151,271,1516,1540]" captionTargetBox="[239,1342,517,1470]" captionTargetId="figure-359@9.[188,1398,473,1514]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURES 23–26. Stegana (Steganina) pilosella sp. nov., ♂: 23. Epandrium, surstylus and cercus (lateral view); 24. surstylus (frontal view); 25. 10th sternite; 26. hypandrium, gonopods, aedeagus and aedeagal apodeme (ventral view) (For abbreviations see Figures 1–6. Scale bars: 0.1 mm)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5321880" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5321880/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="46">Fig. 24</figureCitation>
). Cercus with sporadic pubescence (
<figureCitation box="[1262,1354,1849,1875]" captionStart="FIGURES 23–26" captionStartId="9.[151,271,1516,1540]" captionTargetBox="[239,1342,517,1470]" captionTargetId="figure-359@9.[188,1398,473,1514]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURES 23–26. Stegana (Steganina) pilosella sp. nov., ♂: 23. Epandrium, surstylus and cercus (lateral view); 24. surstylus (frontal view); 25. 10th sternite; 26. hypandrium, gonopods, aedeagus and aedeagal apodeme (ventral view) (For abbreviations see Figures 1–6. Scale bars: 0.1 mm)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5321880" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5321880/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="46">Fig. 23</figureCitation>
). Plate between hypandrium and aedeagus lacking pubescence, with 1 sensillum (
<figureCitation box="[1022,1110,1887,1913]" captionStart="FIGURES 23–26" captionStartId="9.[151,271,1516,1540]" captionTargetBox="[239,1342,517,1470]" captionTargetId="figure-359@9.[188,1398,473,1514]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURES 23–26. Stegana (Steganina) pilosella sp. nov., ♂: 23. Epandrium, surstylus and cercus (lateral view); 24. surstylus (frontal view); 25. 10th sternite; 26. hypandrium, gonopods, aedeagus and aedeagal apodeme (ventral view) (For abbreviations see Figures 1–6. Scale bars: 0.1 mm)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5321880" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5321880/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="46">Fig. 26</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
